{
  "stem": "7458.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we-- we were a very large family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It has been said that rather than the-- the Jewish people keeping the Shabbat, the Shabbat had kept the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think that there is a great deal of truth to it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Life in the shtetl was terribly difficult.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Aside from the anti-Semitism and the isolation, which I will talk about, I'm sure, later, people worked day and night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was very difficult to work in a tannery and support a family of eight children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, it was more than just eight children, because in most families grandparents lived in the house with you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And aunts and uncles who never got married lived in the house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So there were many mouths to feed and life was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And people worked 12-, 14-, 15-hour days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But, came Friday afternoon, life changed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A quiet befell the town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Men would stop working.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They would go to the bathhouse, to shower and clean and get ready for the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then they would come home, take their children, and walk to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father never came home from the synagogue without bringing at least one, and sometimes two or three, guests for the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Those were called orchim, people-- they were religious students or traveling scholars who did not have a place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were no hotels, so many of them ended up coming as guests for the entire weekend.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There were also, in some towns, and occasionally they would come to Jasionovka, there were yeshivot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Those are religious schools for young men.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they would have no way of existing, except by being supported by the townspeople.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
